 way to avoid the terrible and unpredictable effects of wars. Violent Alternatives to War: Justifying Actions Against Contemporary Terrorism engages in a moral discussion of the challenges associated with violent alternatives to war when confronting terrorism and suggests a comprehensive approach to how this form of violence can be legitimized and how it ought to be used against this contemporary threat.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aGerechter Krieg. 4aTerrorismus. 4aTerrorismusbekämpfung. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  aAlternatives to War.  aJust War Theory.  aPolitical Violence.  aTerrorism.0 cEPUBz97831107300050 cprintz978311073128640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311072989440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110729894423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110729894/original  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK